benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/catalog - Delete all versions for a per tenant catalog

gaps: Authorization: No test explicitly covers 403 Forbidden vs 401 Unauthorized responses
Caching behavior: no tests around ETag/Cache-Control headers
Rate limiting/throttling: no tests for bursts or throttling behavior
Explicit soft-delete behavior vs permanent delete: not clearly distinguished in tests
Pagination: not applicable for DELETE here, but no explicit note on handling very large deletions beyond performance test
Explicit non-existent resource scenarios beyond tenant existence (e.g., deleting catalog for tenant with catalog already deleted but tenant still exists)
recommendations: Add a test distinguishing 401 vs 403 to verify proper authorization failures
Introduce caching-related checks (ETag/If-None-Match or Cache-Control headers) if applicable to this endpoint
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure system resilience under burst DELETE requests
Clarify and test soft-delete vs hard-delete semantics if the API supports both, and add tests accordingly
Add explicit scenario for tenant with catalog already deleted but tenant exists to validate idempotency and correct status codes
